<div class='communityQuestionAndAnswer'>
<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<a href="/questions/1179369-i-m-on-the-portion-related-to-freud-s">I&#39;m on the portion related to Freud&#39;s theory and how Seth tries to disprove Freud&#39;s theory - &quot;we use our errors - the ways we misspeak or miswrite, to reveal our subconscious desires frequently sexual&quot;. 

Couldn&#39;t someone argue that Freud was not referring to typos through keyboards as we know these are common and rather typos with actual handwriting? This is a major difference and Seth would lose strength</a>
</div>
<div class='communityQAFooter questionFooter'>
<ul class='questionFooterActions'>
<li class='footerItem like'>
<span class='likeItContainer' id='like_container_community_question_1179369'><a id="like_count_community_question_1179369" rel="nofollow" href="/rating/voters/1179369?resource_type=CommunityQuestion"><span class="likesCount">12 likes</span></a>&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;<a rel="nofollow" class="jsLike like_it" href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/new?remember=true&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F28512671-everybody-lies">like</a></span>

</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionTimestamp'>
